[{"id":"VR733461","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of a curve and 2 data points in a plane. The horizontal axis is labeled “Good X,” and the numbers 0 through 5, in increments of 1, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Good Y,” and the numbers 0 through 8, in increments of 1, are indicated. The curve begins at the coordinates 0 comma 8 and moves downward and to the right, gradually at first and then more steeply, and ends at coordinates 5 comma 0. Two points lie on the curve at the following coordinates: point M at 2 comma 7, and point Z at 4 comma 4.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR733461.g05.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The graph provided shows the production possibilities curve for a country’s economy. The economy is currently producing at point Z. What is the opportunity cost of changing production to point M?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR733461_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">3 units of Good Y</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">8 units of Good Y</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">3 units of Good X</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">4 units of Good X</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">2 units of Good X</p>"],"answer":4}]